  "body": "<!--\r\nNOTE: \r\n- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**What is your question?**\r\n<!--A clear and concise description of what the problem is.-->\r\nWhen we find peer, it get's stored in peer store and persisted on disk. When we restart we loose a lot of time probing those same peers that doesn't support status rpc protocol (maybe different chain or something).\r\n\r\nShould we delete peer from peer store on unsupported protocol? Would be even better if we could keep blacklist in peerstore so we don't attempt to connect again",
