    "body": "I think we should set up peer metadata (score, protocol support, etc) in the metadata store (so its persisted, rather than delete peers. There's also the [`ProtoBook`](https://github.com/libp2p/js-libp2p/blob/master/src/peer-store/proto-book.js) that might be persisting supported protocols already, we might look into that.\r\n\r\nIf we delete bad peers, we risk discv5 continuously re-sending that peer to libp2p.",
